<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/9030> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #9030" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/7> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "p. 746, footnote 245" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/7267> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #7267" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/5> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Praetor, uncertain date. Gellius (13.20.12), our only source, states that this son of the consul of 118 (10) was curule aedile and praetor, and died in Gallia Narbonensis, but makes no mention of a provincial command. Dates are uncertain, but twenty-five to thirty years after the father's consulship is not unreasonable, and his offices probably precede the Social War (MRR 2.13, 18, and 22). See Gabba, Republican Rome 66, no. 92 (Praetor 78?); Badian, Mel. Piganiol 906-918.\n" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/3819> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #3819" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Governor of Narbonese Gaul, where he died (Gell. 13.20.12; see 94, Aediles, and note 3). See D.-G. 5.162, no. 18." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/3786> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #3786" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Gell. 13.20.12. See 94, Aediles and note 4; and 91, Promagistrates." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/3748> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #3748" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Gell. 13.20.12. See 92, Praetors, and 91, Promagistrates; and D.-G. 5.162, no. 18." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/3747> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #3747" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "2 All dates in the career of this Cato remain uncertain. It is probable that he died before the Social war while governor of Transalpine Gaul. The latest date for his aedileship would be 94, and for his praetorship, 92. " .
